import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Body_Mass__g_'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['Body_Mass__g_'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['Body_Mass__g_'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['Body_Mass__g_'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Body_Mass__g_'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Body Mass (g)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Body Mass?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['Species'] == 'Adelie']['Beak_Length__mm_'], 
                data[data['Species'] == 'Chinstrap']['Beak_Length__mm_'], 
                data[data['Species'] == 'Gentoo']['Beak_Length__mm_']], 
               labels=['Adelie', 'Chinstrap', 'Gentoo'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Species')
    ax.set_ylabel('Beak Length (mm)')
    ax.set_title('How does Beak Length vary across different Species?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Beak_Depth__mm_'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data[data['Island'] == 'Biscoe']['Beak_Depth__mm_'], alpha=0.5, label='Biscoe')
    ax.hist(data[data['Island'] == 'Dream']['Beak_Depth__mm_'], alpha=0.5, label='Dream')
    ax.hist(data[data['Island'] == 'Torgersen']['Beak_Depth__mm_'], alpha=0.5, label='Torgersen')
    ax.axvline(data[data['Island'] == 'Biscoe']['Beak_Depth__mm_'].mean(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Biscoe Mean')
    ax.axvline(data[data['Island'] == 'Dream']['Beak_Depth__mm_'].mean(), color='orange', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Dream Mean')
    ax.axvline(data[data['Island'] == 'Torgersen']['Beak_Depth__mm_'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Torgersen Mean')
    ax.set_xlabel('Beak Depth (mm)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Beak Depth by Island?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['Species', 'Sex']]
    data = data.groupby(['Species', 'Sex']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.pivot(index='Species', columns='Sex', values='counts')
    data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution across different Species?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Gender', loc='upper right')
    plt.xlabel('Species')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
